sub_title: Technical Lead at Fugro | Geospatial Engineer
summary:
I am a motivated and enthusiastic person, who truly believes that doing small things with great love and passion is the key to success in life.

With a M.Sc. degree in Geoscience and Remote Sensing at TU Delft and an extensive background in Surveying and Geospatial Engineering, I am currently working as a Trajectory and Calibration Leader at Fugro.

projects: [{'title': 'M.Sc. Geoscience and Remote Sensing Fieldwork - Iceland', 'date': {'start': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'description': 'The fieldwork of the M.Sc. Geoscience and Remote Sensing at TU Delft was conducted in close collaboration with the University of Iceland.\nThe group project was about designing a field campaign for the purpose of measuring natural geophysical processes (mass displacements due to seismic/volcanic activity and ground water circulation), as well as human induced deformations due to the activity of geothermal power plants. A thorough analysis on the measured data was carried on in order to provide deep insight on the rate of deformation at various spatial and temporal scales.\nThe related surveys comprised a combination of different techniques that were both remotely sensed (InSAR, atmospheric remote sensing) and on-field (GNSS, levelling, tachymetry with total station, gravimetry).', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Pablo', 'last_name': 'Secco', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Technical Lead at Fugro | Geospatial Engineer'}]}]
